name: market for biomethane, high pressure | biomethane, high pressure | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/22846/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset describes the energy requirements and the emissions of the high pressure distribution network of biomethane. This dataset is based on the dataset "market for natural gas, high pressure, CH". Modelling of network losses and energy requirements are adopted from the latter dataset:;Total network losses are based on published data, repartition of losses on high and low pressure network on calculations with data for other countries.;For biomethane no long distance high pressure pipeline transport within Switzerland is taken into account. Biomethane is produced domestically in Switzerland and leaves the purification plant at a pressure of 5 bar. It is therefore assumed to be fed directly into the high pressure distribition network.;For background documentation to the original dataset "market for natural gas, high pressure, CH" see also: ;2007, Faist Emmenegger, M., Heck, T., Jungbluth, N., Erdgas, Dones R., Sachbilanzen von Energiesystemen. Final report No. 6 ecoinvent data v2.0, 6, Dübendorf and Villigen, CH, Swiss Centre for LCI, PSI, 3, accessible through the ecoinvent website.;Faist Emmenegger M., Del Duce A., Moreno Ruiz E., Brunner F., (2017). Update of the European natural gas supply chains. Ecoinvent, Zürich, Switzerland.

The activity starts wtih the methane being fed into the high pressure network for transmission and distribution.

The activity ends with the methane delivered to the conuming entity or to the connection to a network at different pressure level.
category: D:Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply/35:Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply/352:Manufacture of gas; distribution of gaseous fuels through mains/3520:Manufacture of gas; distribution of gaseous fuels through mains

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Energy requirements are based on environmental report of Italian company. Total leakages are specific for CH; the share of high pressure leakages in total leakage are calculated using German data. See dataset "market for natural gas, high pressure, CH, 2000"
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Biomethane is produced domestically in Switzerland by purification of biogas. It leaves the purification plants at a pressure of 5 bar and is fed into the high-pressure distribution network. This dataset models the distribution of exclusively biogas. Other market datasets for the exclusive distribution of natural gas as well as the mixed distribution of gas from fossil and biogenic sources are available.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Dataset extrapolated from the "market for natural gas, high pressure, CH, 2000" and adapted for the context of biomethane distribution in Switzerland.

exchanges.description:
Leakage emissions: calculated based on the average compostion of biomethane from biogas purification in Switzerland (0.0068kgN/m3), the average density of the biomethane (0.72kg/m3) and the average leakage rate of 0.019% as defined for natural gas distribution in Western European countries (Faist-Emmenegger, 2017).

Reference(s):
Compostion and density of biomethane were calculated as production volume weighted average of  the compostions and densities specified for the ecoinvent datasets representing
biogas purification by amino washing
biogas purification by membrane technique
biogas purification by PSA

Faist Emmenegger M., Del Duce A., Moreno Ruiz E., Brunner F., (2017). Update of the European natural gas supply chains. Ecoinvent, Zürich, Switzerland.
